Class Move.CastleMove

java.lang.Object
engine.forBoard.Move
engine.forBoard.Move.CastleMove
Direct Known Subclasses:
Move.KingSideCastleMove, Move.QueenSideCastleMove
Enclosing class:
Move
abstract static class Move.CastleMove extends Move
The CastleMove class represents a move that involves castling, which is a special king and rook move. This abstract class provides the base functionality for king-side and queen-side castling moves.
Author:
Aaron Ho

    • CastleMove

      CastleMove(Board board, Piece pieceMoved, int destinationCoordinate, Rook castleRook, int castleRookStart, int castleRookDestination)
      Constructs a CastleMove instance with the provided board, moving piece, destination coordinate, castle rook, and rook start and destination positions.
      Parameters:
      board - The chess board on which the move is made.
      pieceMoved - The piece being moved (usually the king).
      destinationCoordinate - The coordinate to which the piece is moved.
      castleRook - The rook involved in the castling move.
      castleRookStart - The starting position of the castle rook.
      castleRookDestination - The destination position of the castle rook.

      public Board execute()
